SENATE RESOLUTION 451
By McNally
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend the employees of the
Office of the Chief Clerk of the Senate of the
2026 Legislative Session.
WHEREAS, we wish to recognize our Senate staff members, all of whom work long
hours, without complaint and often under trying conditions, in service of this General Assembly;
and
WHEREAS, these outstanding public servants perform their essential duties splendidly,
not for personal gain or glory, but rather for the satisfaction of helping to make Tennessee an
even better place to live; and
WHEREAS, much like the venerable postman of days of yore, neither snow nor rain nor
heat nor gloom of demanding Senators stays these faithful employees from the swift completion
of their appointed duties, and usually many times over; and
WHEREAS, the members of the Senate would truly be lost without the invaluable
services of the following Senate staff members; and
WHEREAS, the outstanding employees of the Senate Clerk's office, who serve under
the astute guidance of Chief Clerk of the Senate Russell Humphrey, include Deputy Chief Clerk
Alan Whittington, Journal Clerk Nanette Mitchell, Assistant Clerk Amy Darnall, Senior Advisor to
the Clerk Jake Rose, and Senate Scheduling Clerk Faiza Ferej; and
WHEREAS, the stellar staff of the Senate Engrossing Office, who serve under the expert
guidance of Chief Engrossing Clerk of the Senate Jordan Young, are Senate Engrossing Clerks
Maggie Herndon, Beverly Williams, and Hannah Davis, as well as Senate Engrossing Proofers
Gene Lass, Layla Velazquez, and Tyler Wilcox; and
SR0451
018667
- 1 -

WHEREAS, the standout employees of the Senate Audio/Visual crew who ensure that
things run smoothly and that live and archived broadcasts are always available include Jesse
Alvey, Kirk Sumner, and Raymond Temple; and
WHEREAS, the exemplary gentlemen who ably serve as the Senate Sergeants at Arms
include Chief Sergeant at Arms Ronnie Townes and Mark Davanport, Matt Hays, Bruce
Jackson, Robert Schlafly, and John Schuler; and
WHEREAS, during the 2026 Legislative Session, the Office of the Chief Clerk of the
Senate employed a number of bill clerks to provide a variety of services to the members of the
Senate; those bill clerks are Gabe Amick, Matthew Blessington, Slone Carr, Payton Corlew,
Paizha George, Alex Kolesnikoff, and Reem Wolde; and
WHEREAS, these superlative Senate staffers are essential to the efficient and orderly
operation of this General Assembly, and it is fitting that we express our deep appreciation for
the professional services they render so competently and so cheerfully; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we honor and commend the
employees of the Office of the Chief Clerk of the Senate for the diligent and proficient manner in
which they perform their respective duties, their dedication to public service as evidenced by
their willingness to work long after normal office hours, and their unwavering loyalty to the
members of the Senate.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy.
